1 多元统计基础(M.Statistics Fundamentals)


1.1 基本概念


  • 总体(Population):Every possible individual element that we are interested in measuring.


  • 样本(Sample):A portion of the population.


  • 参数(Parameter):A parameter is a number that describes some characteristic of a population.


  • 统计量(Statistic):A statistic is a number that describes some characteristic of a sample.


1.2 抽样方法和误差


1.2.1 抽样方法(常用)


  • 【参考文献(Reference)】


    • 杨卫婷.民间体育游戏对大班幼儿社会情感能力的影响研究[D].上海师范大学,2025.DOI:10.27312/d.cnki.gshsu.2025.001645.(P20)


    • 赵雨婷.短距离游泳运动员功能性准备活动的设计与应用[D].北京体育大学,2020.DOI:10.26961/d.cnki.gbjtu.2020.000491.(P23)

    • 杨海峰,寿碧琪,邵一宇.杭州市富阳区老年高血压患者脑卒中高危人群现状及危险因素[J].江苏预防医学,2024,35(04):435-438.DOI:10.13668/j.issn.1006-9070.2024.04.008.


    • 赵雨.某社区老年人社会健康现状及其相关因素研究[D].吉林大学,2025.DOI:10.27162/d.cnki.gjlin.2025.001491.(P11)


  • 概率抽样方法(Probability Sampling Methods)


    • 简单随机抽样(Simple random sample):Every member of a population has an equal chance of being selected to be in the sample.


    • 分层抽样(Stratified random sample):Split a population into groups. Randomly select some members from each group to be in the sample.


    • 整群抽样(Cluster random sample):Split a population into clusters. Randomly select some of the clusters and include all members from those clusters in the sample.


    • 系统抽样(Systematic random sample):Put every member of a population into some order. Choosing a random starting point and select every nth member to be in the sample.


  • 非概率抽样(Non-Probability Sampling Methods)


    • 偶遇


    • 判断


    • 推荐


    • 便利


1.2.2 误差


  • 误差 = 测量值 - 真实值


  • 常见误差： 随机误差、过失误差、系统误差、抽样误差


  • 证据强度：不同测量方式所提供证据的强度（或效度）存在差异，源于其测量误差的来源与可控性（识别、量化、预防或校正的可行性与难易程度）差异。


    • 主观量表（测量心理潜变量）：误差来源复杂（系统误差与随机误差并存），直接可控性低，需依赖严谨的量表设计与复杂的统计方法来验证与校正。


    • 行为测量、生理测量等（测量可直接观测的显变量）：误差来源结构清晰，直接可控性高，通常可通过标准化程序直接预防或量化。


  • 如何提升量表的证据强度/效度：


    • 数据清洗与项目分析


    • 信、效度检验（内部一致性信度，重测信度；结构效度，聚敛效度和区分效度)


    在现代测量理论中，效度被视为一系列证据的整合，而非单一统计指标（Messick, 1989；AERA et al., 2014）。

    Validity evidence based on internal structure, including factor structure, convergent validity, and discriminant validity.


    • 共同方法偏差的程序控制与统计诊断


  • 量表误差 ➢ 信度检验 ➢➢ 效度检验 ➢➢➢ 推论可信度


  • 误差与测量可靠性的统计学理解

    • Marital Status: Single, Married, Divorced, Widowed

    • Education Level: Primary, Junior Secondary, Senior Secondary, Bachelor’s, Master’s, PHD


    • Final Ranking: Champion(Gold Medalist), Runner-up(Silver Medalist), Third place(Bronze Medalist)


    • Satisfaction: Very satisfied, satisfied, neutral, unsatisfied, very unsatisfied
    • ( Note:As items within a scale, satisfaction ratings are frequently treated as continuous data.)

1.5.1 集中趋势量


Measures of Central Tendency

  • 平均数(Average, M)

    • \(\overline{x} = \frac{ \Sigma x_{i} }{n}\)


  • 中位数(Median, Mdn)

    • \(M_{e} =\begin{cases}\frac{x_{n} + x_{n+1} }{2} & x \sim odd\\ x_{ \frac{n+1}{2} } & x \sim even\end{cases}\)


  • 众数(Mode)


1.5.2 离散趋势量


Measures of Dispersion

  • 全距(Range)
    • \(R = x_{max} - x_{min}\)


  • 四分位距(Interquartile Range, IQR)

    • Q1、Q2、Q3

    • IQR = Q3 - Q1

    • Mild-Outliers: (< Q1 - 1.5IQR) or (> Q3 + 1.5IQR)

    • Extreme-Outliers: (< Q1 - 3IQR) or (> Q3 + 3IQR)

    • 注：如果存在特异值，最大值（最小值）为去除特异值后剩余数据的最大值（最小值），箱线图辅助说明。


  • 方差/标准差(Variance/Standard Deviation, SD)


    • \(s = \sqrt{ \frac{ \Sigma ( x_{i} - \overline{x} )^{2} }{n-1} }\)


  • 变异系数(CV)

    • \(CV = \frac{s}{ \overline{x} } \times 100\%\)

1.7 置信区间


Confidence Interval


  • 【参考文献(Reference)】


    • 刘卓筱.八周篮球运动对七年级学生执行功能和情绪稳定性的影响研究[D].上海体育大学,2024.DOI:10.27315/d.cnki.gstyx.2024.000463.(P26-CI)


  • A Confidence Interval(CI) is a range of values[ LLCI, ULCI ] that is likely to contain a population parameter with a certain level of confidence.

(Note:LLCI: Lower Limit of the Confidence Interval; ULCI: Upper Limit of the Confidence Interval.)


  • Confidence Interval[ LLCI , ULCI ] = (point estimate) +/- (critical value)*(standard error)
